# Force LF line endings repo-wide for every text file so that contributors on any OS
# pack the same bytes the release workflow does on Linux. Without this, a Windows
# checkout with the default `core.autocrlf=true` converts source files to CRLF, which
# changes Roslyn's embedded source-file SHA in the PDB and propagates into the .dll bytes
# — silently breaking byte-for-byte reproducibility against the published .nupkg.
*               text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: leave alone, never normalize.
*.png           binary
*.jpg           binary
*.jpeg          binary
*.ico           binary
*.gif           binary
*.pdf           binary
*.snk           binary
*.pfx           binary

# Container test vectors / binary fixtures: byte-exact, never normalize.
*.pqfe          binary
*.bin           binary
